  "why": "The paper goes beyond simply reporting failures: it provides statistical analyses of which misuse categories and target models are most vulnerable (Fig. 4 / Jailbreak % by category), evaluates transferability across models (Table VI) and defended performance (Table VIII), and performs multiple ablations (attacker model, system-prompt components, stream depth) that link attack success to specific design choices. It also explicitly attributes differences in success rates to differences in safety fine-tuning and to the semantic (interpretable) nature of PAIR prompts. However, the paper does not analyze model internals (e.g., neuron activations) or deeply diagnose low-level causes such as spurious token features or specific dataset biases; its explanations remain at the level of statistical patterns and alignment/fine-tuning differences rather than mechanistic root causes. Thus it provides partial diagnostic insight but not a full explanatory account of underlying model vulnerabilities.",
